description:
&lt;p&gt;Please note that full time and part time working arrangements will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NHS Long Term Plan commits to national coverage of Integrated Care Systems (ICSs) by April 2021. ICSs are a way of creating shared local responsibility for service transformation and management and building wider partnerships with local government and other community partners. In line with the new operating model, regional teams are at the forefront of delivering this change and working with systems to help them become ICSs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The System Support team, part of the national System Transformation Team, are recruiting a band 8c Senior Programme Lead post, aligned to the North regions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Programme Lead (System Support) role will have responsibility for a portfolio of projects aimed at developing and supporting integrated care systems (one in the North East &amp; Yorkshire Region and the North West Region). The posts will require close working with other parts of the System Transformation team and other national NHSE/I teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is an exciting opportunity for an experienced transformation expert to work on a key Long Term Plan priority and build strong relationships with senior members of local health and care systems. Candidates will need to demonstrate delivery expertise in either STPs or ICSs and in working in complex environments with exceptional communications and partnership working skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The roles will usually be based at Quarry House (Leeds) and usually requires frequent travel, however, we are currently working remotely aligned to government guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
